<TITLE> Grade 8, scholarship exams together this year </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 13 (bdnews24.com) The government has decided to hold grade eight final and scholarship exams jointly using a common set of questions all over the country this year. The decision came from meeting of the education ministry meeting on Wednesday. A convening committee was formed headed by the director general of secondary and higher education directorate, with chairmen of eight secondary and higher education boards, of Bangladesh Madrasah Education Board and director general of Directorate of Vocational Educational Training as members. The directors of SESDP and SEQAEP projects, representatives of the education ministry and primary and mass education ministry are the other members. The committee can co-opt more members if necessary. The Directorate of Secondary and Higher Education is to provide secretarial support to the committe
